<body id="door_closer___installation">

    <h1 class="title topictitle1" id="ariaid-title1">Door Closer - Installation</h1>

    
    <div class="body taskbody"><p class="shortdesc">Installation of the <em class="ph i"><span class="ph">Door Closer</span></em>.</p>

        <ol class="ol steps"><li class="li step">
                <span class="ph cmd">Put the new <em class="ph i"><span class="ph">Door Closer</span></em> in the correct position (see <a class="xref" href="#door_closer___installation__Door_Closer">Figure 1</a>).</span>
                
                    <div class="fig fignone" id="door_closer___installation__Door_Closer"><span class="figcap"><span class="fig--title-label">Figure 1. </span>Door Closer</span>
                        
                        <img class="image" src="../images/ICN-ACTA-AA-XX-X-XXX-A-D2714-06367-A-01-1.png" />
                    </div>

                
            </li>
<li class="li step">
                <span class="ph cmd">Fasten the six screws to the door and to the ground shelter frame (see item 1
                    in <a class="xref" href="cm_door_closer___removal.html#door_closer___removal__Door_Closer_load_unload">Figure 1</a>).</span>
            </li>
<li class="li step">
                <span class="ph cmd">Pre-load the <em class="ph i"><span class="ph">Door Closer</span></em> (see item 2 in <a class="xref" href="cm_door_closer___removal.html#door_closer___removal__Door_Closer_load_unload">Figure 1</a>).</span>
            </li>
<li class="li step">
                <span class="ph cmd"><strong class="ph b">Adjust the <em class="ph i"><span class="ph">Door Closer</span></em>:</strong></span>
                <ol type="a" class="ol substeps">
                    <li class="li substep substepexpand">
                        <span class="ph cmd">Adjust the <strong class="ph b">Spring Power</strong> (see right side in <a class="xref" href="#door_closer___installation__Adjustment_of_Door_Closer">Figure 2</a>).</span>
                        <div class="itemgroup info">On the right-hand side the <em class="ph i">Spring Power</em> can be adjusted by
                            tightening or loosening the screw. It is used to adjust the spring
                            strength (force to close the door). Clockwise gives the closer more
                            closing power (which also makes the door harder to open), and turning
                            the screw counter clockwise, will give the door less closing strength
                            (and makes the door easier to open).</div>
                    </li>

                    <li class="li substep substepexpand">
                        <span class="ph cmd">Adjust the <strong class="ph b">Back Check</strong> (see item 1 in <a class="xref" href="#door_closer___installation__Adjustment_of_Door_Closer">Figure 2</a>).</span>
                        <div class="itemgroup info">The <em class="ph i">Back Check</em> is used to slow the door down if someone throws
                            the door open, or if the wind were to catch the door, and blow it open.
                            Back check is used to slow the door down, not to stop the door.</div>
                    </li>

                    <li class="li substep substepexpand">
                        <span class="ph cmd">Adjust the <strong class="ph b">Latch Speed</strong> (see item 3 in <a class="xref" href="#door_closer___installation__Adjustment_of_Door_Closer">Figure 2</a>).</span>
                        <div class="itemgroup info">The <em class="ph i">Latch Speed Valve</em> can be adjusted to control how fast the
                            door closes for the last few centimeters.</div>
                    </li>

                    <li class="li substep substepexpand">
                        <span class="ph cmd">Adjust the <strong class="ph b">Main Speed</strong> (see item 2 in <a class="xref" href="#door_closer___installation__Adjustment_of_Door_Closer">Figure 2</a>).</span>
                        <div class="itemgroup info">The <em class="ph i">Main Speed Screw</em> controls the main closing speed of the
                            door. The main speed is the area from the door in the wide open position
                            down to the last 15Â° before the latch. Turning the valve clockwise will
                            make the door close slower. Turning the valve counter clockwise will
                            cause the door to close faster.</div>
                    </li>

                </ol>

                
                    <div class="fig fignone" id="door_closer___installation__Adjustment_of_Door_Closer"><span class="figcap"><span class="fig--title-label">Figure 2. </span>Adjustment of Door Closer</span>
                        
                        <img class="image" src="../images/ICN-ACTA-AA-XX-X-XXX-A-D2714-06368-A-01-1.png" />
                    </div>

                
            </li>
</ol>

    </div>

</body>
